03:44.309 --> 03:45.810
Your shoulder flaring?

03:45.894 --> 03:46.978
No.

03:47.478 --> 03:48.688
You winced.

03:48.771 --> 03:49.772
I didn't wince.

03:49.981 --> 03:51.441
You grimaced.

03:52.817 --> 03:55.069
My shoulder doesn't hurt, Gus.

04:01.200 --> 04:03.453
How long has it been hurting?

04:07.457 --> 04:09.876
Perry wants me
to start tomorrow.

04:11.085 --> 04:12.962
You got to be kidding.

04:14.505 --> 04:16.089
You're not doing it.

04:16.173 --> 04:19.385
No way. It's the end
of a shitty season.

04:19.469 --> 04:20.720
I'm gonna talk to Perry.

04:20.803 --> 04:24.390
Sit down, sit down. Relax.

04:24.474 --> 04:26.225
Sir, drink?

04:26.309 --> 04:27.560
Thank you.

04:27.644 --> 04:30.813
It's a throwaway, Billy.
It means nothing.

04:32.148 --> 04:33.858
Not to the Red Sox.

04:36.986 --> 04:39.781
If I see you wince
even one time...

04:39.864 --> 04:41.908
Oh, God.

04:44.786 --> 04:47.538
I've got the ugliest wife
in the league.

04:49.624 --> 04:52.543
That hurts.
It hurt my feeling.

04:55.046 --> 04:57.006
Buckle your seat belt.

05:09.686 --> 05:12.647
Are we expecting
Ms. Aubrey this evening?

05:12.730 --> 05:14.023
We are.

05:14.857 --> 05:16.192
What name
am I registered under?

05:16.275 --> 05:17.777
Mike Nelson.

05:17.860 --> 05:20.279
The <i>Sea Hunt</i> fellow,
you know.

05:20.363 --> 05:21.698
All right.

05:21.781 --> 05:26.202
Tell the desk that I don't
want to talk to anybody
except her, all right?

05:26.285 --> 05:31.332
Fitch, tonight,
everything has to be perfect.

05:31.416 --> 05:33.418
Have I ever let you down,
Mr. Chapel?

06:04.365 --> 06:07.243
This is Mr. Chapel.
Have there been any messages?

06:08.244 --> 06:09.287
No?

06:11.414 --> 06:12.665
Thanks.

06:31.851 --> 06:34.395
<i>Hi, this is Jane.
Leave a message</i>

06:34.479 --> 06:37.315
<i>and I'll get back to you.
Thanks a lot. Bye-bye.</i>

06:37.398 --> 06:39.817
Jane, it's Billy.
I'm worried now,

06:40.777 --> 06:41.778
so please call.

06:45.281 --> 06:46.783
Are you there?

07:50.471 --> 07:53.307
Jesus. I've been banging
out here forever.

07:56.227 --> 07:58.521
What the hell happened to you?

08:00.398 --> 08:02.316
You weren't at the gym.

08:04.402 --> 08:05.570
Is Jane here?

08:05.653 --> 08:06.946
No.

08:11.075 --> 08:12.243
Jesus.

08:18.124 --> 08:20.710
Chap, a lot of little bottles
makes a big bottle.

08:20.793 --> 08:23.129
Hey. That could be her.

08:24.755 --> 08:26.090
You got to throw today, chief.

08:26.174 --> 08:29.093
Gus, do me a favor,
all right. Get the door.

08:31.971 --> 08:33.597
Throw some water
on your hair.

08:33.681 --> 08:35.265
It might look like
you took a shower.

08:41.898 --> 08:44.734
No, not at all. He's in
the bathroom back there.

08:49.697 --> 08:50.907
Mr. Wheeler.

08:50.990 --> 08:53.910
Good morning, Billy.
Got a minute?

08:53.993 --> 08:55.369
Yeah, sure.

08:57.622 --> 08:59.624
Not easy to get up here.

09:00.666 --> 09:01.792
They treat me right.

09:01.876 --> 09:03.461
They didn't have you
on the register.

09:03.544 --> 09:05.004
I can't remember
all your names.

09:05.087 --> 09:06.088
Price of fame, huh?

09:09.050 --> 09:10.301
Can I get you something?

09:10.384 --> 09:12.178
No.

09:12.261 --> 09:13.763
Let's just sit.

09:18.059 --> 09:20.102
It's been a rough season.

09:21.729 --> 09:22.980
Yeah.

09:23.105 --> 09:24.190
Always next year.

09:24.273 --> 09:25.274
Not for me.

09:27.235 --> 09:30.446
It's one of those secrets
everybody knows.

09:30.529 --> 09:32.698
What you don't know is
it's official.

09:34.533 --> 09:36.577
Billy, I sold the Tigers.

09:44.085 --> 09:47.046
Well, that's great.

09:47.129 --> 09:48.547
Is it?

09:52.969 --> 09:58.724
Billy, you've been the heart
and soul of this team.

09:58.808 --> 10:00.268
Like family.

10:02.311 --> 10:03.980
All the negotiations,

10:04.355 --> 10:05.940
the bastards
never said a word.

10:09.485 --> 10:10.861
Said what?

10:13.614 --> 10:16.242
They want to trade you
to the Giants.

10:27.044 --> 10:28.170
Wow!

10:32.258 --> 10:33.509
Is that why you're here?

10:33.592 --> 10:34.593
No.

10:36.137 --> 10:38.097
I don't know how to say this.

10:39.140 --> 10:41.851
You know, I've been
watching you for 18 years.

10:43.060 --> 10:48.107
Nothing has given me
more pleasure.

10:48.190 --> 10:51.277
You're like the old boys.
They were golden.

10:52.111 --> 10:53.696
They had that special pride.

10:55.031 --> 10:57.033
When they were done,
they were done.

10:57.700 --> 10:59.702
Nobody had to
show them the door.

11:06.208 --> 11:07.960
Are you saying
I should retire?

11:08.044 --> 11:10.212
Why not?

11:10.296 --> 11:11.922
It wouldn't hurt
the negotiations,

11:12.048 --> 11:14.050
and it'd serve
those sons of bitches right.

11:20.222 --> 11:23.559
I don't know what to say.

11:23.642 --> 11:26.479
You can't tell me
you haven't thought about it.

11:26.562 --> 11:30.900
And you've been smart
with money, right? Right?

11:36.405 --> 11:38.741
I've always been a Tiger.

11:39.241 --> 11:40.785
I know, son.

11:41.827 --> 11:44.080
That's why this is killing me.

11:47.917 --> 11:51.754
You know, my dad bought
this team when I was seven.

11:51.837 --> 11:54.048
I grew up watching the Tigers.

11:54.131 --> 11:55.841
I was gonna leave the team
to my kids,

11:55.925 --> 11:57.718
but they don't
even like baseball.

11:58.094 --> 11:59.970
Everything's changed, Billy.

12:00.096 --> 12:04.266
The players, the fans,
TV rights and arbitrations.

12:04.350 --> 12:07.269
It isn't the same.
The game stinks, and I...

12:08.646 --> 12:11.190
...I can't be
a part of it anymore.

12:22.076 --> 12:24.120
Billy, you want me to...

12:25.496 --> 12:26.580
No.

12:31.585 --> 12:34.255
Hello? Jane.

12:34.338 --> 12:38.259
Where are you?
You're downstairs?

12:38.884 --> 12:40.594
No. Just stay there,
all right?

12:40.678 --> 12:43.139
Just stay where you're at.
I'm on my way down.

12:43.848 --> 12:45.391
What do you want me
to tell them, Billy?

12:45.474 --> 12:47.977
Look, I need more time.
All right?

12:57.278 --> 12:59.238
The game doesn't stink,
Mr. Wheeler.

13:00.489 --> 13:01.490
It's a great game.

13:05.953 --> 13:07.788
Billy, what's up?

13:12.168 --> 13:14.295
I tried to get her
in a cab, Mr. Chapel,

13:14.378 --> 13:18.257
but she said she wanted
to just go and walk
across Central Park.

13:18.340 --> 13:20.342
Go easy
on our boys today, Billy.

13:47.328 --> 13:50.331
Jane, why didn't you wait?

13:52.541 --> 13:54.043
Are you crying?

14:02.343 --> 14:03.427
What's the matter?

14:03.511 --> 14:07.306
They didn't have any Kleenex
in the hotel bathroom.

14:07.389 --> 14:09.225
What's going on, Jane?

14:09.308 --> 14:13.270
I've been sitting in the lobby
for the last two hours.

14:13.354 --> 14:14.730
Doing what?

14:16.982 --> 14:19.318
I'm sorry
I didn't call last night.

14:19.401 --> 14:21.403
I could tell that your voice
was worried and I...

14:21.487 --> 14:23.614
If something's wrong,
just say it, Jane.

14:23.697 --> 14:24.990
I mean, we don't...

14:25.908 --> 14:27.910
We never had to fake it.

14:32.081 --> 14:35.834
I'm leaving.
I'm going to London.

14:41.590 --> 14:42.925
London?

14:43.008 --> 14:47.846
There's a job. A good job.
An editor's position.

14:47.930 --> 14:52.101
And I've been trying to figure
out a way to tell you,

14:52.184 --> 14:54.353
but everything sounds so...

14:56.605 --> 15:00.776
What can I say?
Tell me what to say.

15:04.738 --> 15:06.740
I can't tell you, Billy.

15:09.368 --> 15:12.621
It's all right. I knew it.

15:13.539 --> 15:16.208
The day I met you
five years ago.
What?

15:16.292 --> 15:17.334
You knew what?

15:17.418 --> 15:18.711
You don't need me.

15:20.421 --> 15:23.632
You and the ball and
the diamond, you're perfect.

15:23.757 --> 15:26.093
A perfectly beautiful thing.

15:26.176 --> 15:29.138
You can win or lose the game
all by yourself.

15:33.601 --> 15:34.935
I'm sorry.

15:36.645 --> 15:38.147
I'm so sorry.

15:39.690 --> 15:42.901
Have dinner tonight with me,
Jane, after the game.

15:44.820 --> 15:46.155
We'll go to Mario's.

15:46.238 --> 15:48.282
I have a 6:00 plane.

15:50.075 --> 15:52.703
They wanted me there
a week ago when you called,

15:52.786 --> 15:54.204
and I wanted to see you.

15:54.788 --> 15:56.790
I wanted to say goodbye.

15:59.168 --> 16:00.836
Goodbye, Billy.

16:31.992 --> 16:34.787
<i>Welcome to New York
and to Yankee Stadium</i>

16:34.870 --> 16:38.248
<i>on a crisp and glorious
fall afternoon</i>

16:38.332 --> 16:41.085
<i>where the Yankees try
to win the divisional title</i>

16:41.168 --> 16:43.337
<i>against the Detroit Tigers.</i>

16:43.420 --> 16:46.006
Hi, everybody. I'm Vin Scully,
along with Steve Lyons,

16:46.090 --> 16:49.051
and welcome to our final telecast
of the regular season.

16:50.010 --> 16:51.762
<i>You can smell the fall.</i>

16:51.845 --> 16:54.723
<i>The World Series is
just around the corner.</i>

17:01.563 --> 17:02.940
Mr. Chapel?

17:05.983 --> 17:10.906
Hey. Ken Strout. I was
your batboy a long time ago.

17:10.989 --> 17:12.741
My dad was a Tiger.

17:15.661 --> 17:20.833
Joe Strout. I remember.
How's he doing?

17:20.915 --> 17:23.252
Good. He and Ma are living
in Florida.

17:23.335 --> 17:25.128
He doesn't move
around too easy, though.

17:25.212 --> 17:28.382
He's got bad knees.
You know, a little arthritis.

17:30.092 --> 17:31.343
What? You playing today?

17:31.427 --> 17:33.303
Don't think so.
They just called me up.

17:33.387 --> 17:36.014
Good. Well, good luck to you.

17:36.098 --> 17:39.685
Give your dad my best.
He was a great player.

17:39.768 --> 17:41.812
Oh, thanks. I'll tell him.

17:50.738 --> 17:52.740
<i>Live from
Yankee Stadium in New York,</i>

17:52.823 --> 17:54.908
<i>it's New York
Yankees baseball.</i>

17:54.992 --> 17:57.536
<i>Today, on the next
to last day of the year,</i>

17:57.619 --> 17:59.955
<i>the Yankees have a chance
to clinch the pennant.</i>

18:00.038 --> 18:02.833
<i>To do it, they'll have to beat
Billy Chapel...</i>

18:02.916 --> 18:05.085
Excuse me.
<i>...and the Detroit Tigers.</i>

18:05.169 --> 18:08.380
Excuse me. Could you
turn that off, please?

18:08.464 --> 18:09.840
<i>...as the Yankees are set</i>

18:09.923 --> 18:11.383
<i>to clinch the pennant.</i>
No.

18:11.467 --> 18:12.801
<i>But standing in their way</i>

18:12.885 --> 18:15.262
<i>is the great veteran
right-hander of the Tigers,</i>

18:15.345 --> 18:16.805
<i>Billy Chapel.</i>

18:17.848 --> 18:19.558
Does anybody else know?

18:19.641 --> 18:21.018
No.

18:21.101 --> 18:24.897
Nobody knows nothing.
Not even Perry.

18:24.980 --> 18:28.192
If they knew, that's all
they'd be talking about.

18:31.487 --> 18:33.489
Well, what does Jane say?

18:35.491 --> 18:38.076
Jane's moving to London.

18:38.160 --> 18:40.120
Moving to London? What the...

18:40.746 --> 18:42.956
How are you gonna manage that?

18:43.040 --> 18:44.833
We're not.

18:47.836 --> 18:49.129
Billy...

18:50.923 --> 18:52.674
This ain't your day.

18:57.346 --> 18:59.223
What are you gonna do?

19:02.226 --> 19:03.685
I don't know.

19:08.190 --> 19:10.192
That's Wheeler's nephew.

19:12.110 --> 19:15.113
He sent him down
to get your answer.

19:15.197 --> 19:18.617
Guess he's gonna sit through
the whole game if he has to.

19:18.700 --> 19:20.035
Poor kid.

19:21.203 --> 19:24.039
He doesn't even know
what he's doing here.

20:02.411 --> 20:04.329
<i>Just throw the ball
to the glove, son.</i>

20:04.413 --> 20:05.414
<i>Just play catch.</i>

20:15.674 --> 20:17.175
Now since
you're throwing bullets,

20:17.259 --> 20:19.344
I won't mention
you were an hour late

20:19.428 --> 20:22.222
and I've been trying to figure
out who my pitcher would be

20:22.306 --> 20:23.348
if you didn't show up.

20:23.432 --> 20:25.392
Have I ever not showed?

20:27.144 --> 20:30.480
I mean, in 19 years,
have I ever not showed?

20:32.482 --> 20:33.650
Well, that's true of everyone

20:33.734 --> 20:36.111
till the first time
they don't show.

20:37.154 --> 20:38.864
Billy, I had an idea.

20:38.947 --> 20:39.990
I've pretty much made up
my mind,

20:40.073 --> 20:42.200
but I wanted
to run it by you first.

20:43.118 --> 20:45.370
I want Jimmy to catch today.

20:45.454 --> 20:48.665
I know how you feel about Gus,
but he ain't hitting, Billy.

20:48.749 --> 20:50.959
He ain't hit for a while now.

20:56.089 --> 20:57.633
I haven't said anything,

20:57.716 --> 20:58.842
but we need
the left-handed bat.

20:58.926 --> 21:00.010
I want Gus.

21:00.093 --> 21:03.388
I know. And I'd love to take
one of these goddamn games.

21:03.472 --> 21:04.640
We're not laying down.

21:04.723 --> 21:07.643
We're not gonna be a red carpet
to the Series for these guys.

21:08.936 --> 21:11.813
Gus catches or I don't pitch.

21:12.731 --> 21:15.734
Me and Gus. Nobody else.

21:17.986 --> 21:20.030
I hope you hear me.

21:20.113 --> 21:21.865
Billy, you telling me
how to run this team?

21:21.949 --> 21:24.242
No. But today...

21:25.452 --> 21:28.455
It's me and Gus.
I've never asked you
any other time, okay?

21:29.414 --> 21:30.666
Good.

21:30.749 --> 21:32.459
Glad you agree. Can't argue
about this right now.

21:32.542 --> 21:34.127
Got to warm up.

21:38.674 --> 21:41.218
I'm sorry.
We have a bit of a delay.

21:41.301 --> 21:43.553
We're correcting a bit
of a maintenance problem.

21:43.637 --> 21:46.098
So we don't have
a bit of a crash?

21:47.015 --> 21:48.850
Is there someplace I can stay?

21:48.934 --> 21:52.062
Yes. The Premier Lounge is
down there on your right.

21:52.354 --> 21:53.563
Thanks.

21:54.356 --> 21:55.357
<i>As the sun goes down,</i>

21:55.440 --> 21:57.693
<i>it'll actually be an easier
time to hit for both teams.</i>

21:57.776 --> 21:59.945
<i>And now talking
about shadows and sunlight</i>

22:00.028 --> 22:02.447
<i>that might very well
sum up Billy Chapel.</i>

22:02.531 --> 22:05.283
<i>Long has he stood
in the brilliant sunshine</i>

22:05.367 --> 22:07.369
<i>in his great 19-year career,</i>

22:07.452 --> 22:11.206
<i>but now, battling back from
an 8 and 11 record this year,</i>

22:11.289 --> 22:13.542
<i>trying to find his way
out of the shadows,</i>

22:13.709 --> 22:14.960
<i>back into the sunlight.</i>

22:15.043 --> 22:18.422
<i>He'll be facing Mike Robinson,
followed by Jonathan Warble</i>

22:18.505 --> 22:19.965
and then Sam Tuttle.

22:20.048 --> 22:22.050
Bottom of the first inning,
no score,

22:22.134 --> 22:23.802
and the Yankees coming up.

22:44.322 --> 22:46.158
What's he looking at?

22:48.618 --> 22:52.873
He's looking at the clouds.

22:54.082 --> 22:57.210
You okay, Chap? Chappie!

22:58.587 --> 22:59.880
You okay?

23:07.596 --> 23:12.976
<i>Catching, Number
27. Gus Sinski. Number 27.</i>

23:13.935 --> 23:16.730
<i>At shortstop, Number 7.</i>

23:16.813 --> 23:18.190
Trying to take my hand off?

23:18.273 --> 23:19.775
Sorry.

23:19.858 --> 23:21.401
Just let me set
for that juice.

23:21.485 --> 23:22.861
Warn me or something.

23:23.570 --> 23:26.656
I'm gonna throw a little
harder than usual today.

23:26.740 --> 23:28.575
There's your warning.

23:28.658 --> 23:30.952
Chap, don't throw it away
too early.

23:34.539 --> 23:36.792
Today I'm throwing hard, Gus.

23:38.126 --> 23:40.504
You and me? One more time?

23:43.256 --> 23:44.508
Why not?

23:57.521 --> 24:00.107
We got you, Chapel!
You're done!

24:00.190 --> 24:02.859
We're gonna stick
a fork in you, Chapel!

24:02.943 --> 24:03.944
You're finished!

24:05.112 --> 24:07.739
You are complete.
The Tigers are done!

24:07.823 --> 24:09.616
You're done! You're finished!

24:09.699 --> 24:11.326
Get out of town!

24:12.494 --> 24:14.496
I can always tell
when I'm in New York.

24:16.206 --> 24:19.000
Chapel! Yo, Chapel!

24:19.751 --> 24:21.002
You suck!

24:22.462 --> 24:26.675
You stink on ice!
You couldn't pitch a tent!

24:40.897 --> 24:42.691
<i>Clear the mechanism.</i>

24:54.411 --> 24:55.871
Hello, Mike.

25:00.417 --> 25:02.669
<i>Strike one!</i>

25:06.381 --> 25:08.383
<i>Chapel working
on Robinson.</i>

25:08.466 --> 25:10.844
<i>Bottom of the first inning,
no score.</i>

25:14.055 --> 25:17.142
<i>And there's a little looper
to JosÃ© Garcia. One away.</i>

25:18.393 --> 25:20.854
This is my lucky day.
How are you?

25:20.937 --> 25:22.939
Fine. How you doing?
What'll you have?

25:23.023 --> 25:25.233
The Bud on tap is good.

25:25.734 --> 25:29.404
This is a beautiful day
for the big ballpark
in the Bronx.

25:37.078 --> 25:39.831
<i>Two solid years, and now
a third with the Yankees.</i>

25:39.915 --> 25:41.666
<i>Pretty good breaking ball.
Did get it up...</i>

25:41.750 --> 25:44.544
A lot of guys would be upset
about missing their flight

25:44.628 --> 25:46.213
you know,
delay this and that,

25:46.296 --> 25:48.131
but this works out
beautiful for me.

25:49.591 --> 25:51.968
<i>Chapel trying
to derail the Yankees</i>

25:52.219 --> 25:54.804
<i>and the Yankees trying
to end a season</i>

25:54.888 --> 25:57.724
<i>that has long been finished
by Detroit.</i>

26:06.775 --> 26:09.319
They pushed this guy up
to pitch this game,

26:09.402 --> 26:12.280
so basically we clinch
today and I get to see it.

26:12.364 --> 26:13.365
Beautiful.

26:16.868 --> 26:18.078
Hi. What can I get for you?

26:18.161 --> 26:20.038
Chivas and water.

26:20.121 --> 26:21.706
Okay, here we go.

26:21.790 --> 26:25.043
Everything is...
Look at that. It's early.

26:26.503 --> 26:29.089
You got nuts, chips? Some?

26:29.172 --> 26:30.215
Got those pretzels.

26:30.298 --> 26:31.549
I can make do.

26:31.633 --> 26:32.968
Thank you.

26:34.719 --> 26:36.680
<i>Good fastball
with some movement on it.</i>

26:36.763 --> 26:39.140
<i>Down goes Warble.</i>
He swung at that?

26:39.224 --> 26:40.892
This guy,
he's got nothing now.

26:40.976 --> 26:42.477
It's like, if I was Boston,
I'd be worried.

26:42.560 --> 26:46.064
I'd be like, "What?
Are you throwing the game?"

26:46.147 --> 26:47.983
This guy used to be a monster,
to tell you the truth.

26:48.066 --> 26:52.737
When he first came up,
unhittable. Now he's a junker.

26:53.488 --> 26:56.533
<i>...three years in a row. In
baseball circles, we all know</i>

26:56.616 --> 26:58.493
<i>that there's no love lost
between these two.</i>

26:58.576 --> 26:59.995
<i>They don't like
each other too much.</i>

27:01.288 --> 27:05.500
<i>At third base,
Number 13, Sam Tuttle.</i>

27:07.961 --> 27:09.337
Sam Tuttle.

