29:44.367 --> 29:47.120
<i>Bill Murdie goes
from umpire to referee.</i>

29:47.704 --> 29:49.622
<i>Anytime I played
against this guy,</i>

29:49.706 --> 29:51.124
<i>if he felt like
he had good stuff,</i>

29:51.207 --> 29:52.375
<i>he'd flip you like this.</i>

29:53.001 --> 29:54.919
<i>He'd throw a ball
right over your head</i>

29:55.003 --> 29:57.839
<i>just to let you know,
"I can throw the ball
anywhere I want today."</i>

29:57.922 --> 30:00.758
You know, I've been
a Yankee fan since 1958.

30:00.842 --> 30:03.636
I can name a Yankee
for every number.

30:03.720 --> 30:05.805
Oh, God. Please don't.

30:05.889 --> 30:08.224
Number One: Billy Martin,
Bobby Richardson.

30:08.308 --> 30:12.228
Number Two: Frank "The Crow"
Crosetti and Bobby Murcer.

30:12.312 --> 30:14.314
Number Three: The Babe.
Number Four: Gehrig.

30:14.397 --> 30:16.608
Five: DiMaggio. Six...
Excuse me.

30:16.691 --> 30:18.067
...Clete Boyer, Roy White.

30:18.151 --> 30:19.611
Would you mind?

30:21.488 --> 30:22.947
You can't smoke in a bar.

30:23.031 --> 30:24.532
What, now you can't
talk in a bar?

30:25.408 --> 30:26.451
This ain't church, lady.

30:26.534 --> 30:28.912
<i>Oh, what a restore.
Tuttle back up to the plate.</i>

30:28.995 --> 30:30.288
Two and two!

30:30.371 --> 30:32.749
Same shit, different day?

30:32.832 --> 30:34.459
I'd throw it at you again,

30:34.542 --> 30:37.045
but I'm afraid
Murdie'd run me.

30:42.091 --> 30:43.176
Strike three!

30:43.259 --> 30:44.761
<i>Oh, good breaking ball.</i>

30:44.844 --> 30:46.012
<i>Got him looking.</i>

30:46.095 --> 30:48.431
<i>What a great job
setting up the hitter.</i>

30:48.515 --> 30:49.474
<i>Let's take
another look.</i>

30:49.557 --> 30:51.809
<i>Tuttle looks like a deer
caught in the headlights.</i>

30:51.893 --> 30:53.311
<i>Chapel jelly-legged him.</i>

30:53.394 --> 30:54.687
<i>So at the end of one,</i>

30:54.771 --> 30:56.648
<i>Tigers nothing,
Yankees nothing.</i>

30:56.731 --> 30:58.274
All right. Here we go now.

30:58.358 --> 31:00.985
Four, five, six. Let's get
something started.

31:01.069 --> 31:04.614
JosÃ©, atta-baby. It's all
about positioning. All right?

31:05.907 --> 31:07.700
You got to wait on this guy.

31:07.784 --> 31:09.744
Mike, can I have some water?

31:09.827 --> 31:10.995
Sure thing, Billy.

31:11.079 --> 31:12.622
You all right?

31:16.209 --> 31:18.545
You got it going good
out there.

31:19.754 --> 31:21.965
Make sure you save something.

31:27.595 --> 31:30.098
Birch wants
to play golf tomorrow.

31:34.018 --> 31:37.480
You know, I played golf
with Birch the day I met Jane.

31:39.023 --> 31:40.316
You doing all right?

31:42.318 --> 31:43.861
Yeah.

31:45.280 --> 31:47.949
I'm not hearing them
at all out there.

32:20.106 --> 32:21.941
Yeah, that'll fix it.

32:51.638 --> 32:53.514
I don't need any help.

32:55.350 --> 32:57.852
I can see that.
I can see you got your car

32:57.977 --> 33:00.229
kicked completely
into submission.

33:00.313 --> 33:02.315
I mean it. Just go away.

33:04.275 --> 33:07.028
I can always tell
when I'm in New York.

33:10.198 --> 33:12.909
Do you really know
anything about cars?

33:21.000 --> 33:22.293
You want me to have
a look at it?

33:22.377 --> 33:25.922
Okay. It's not mine.
It's just a trashy rental.

33:26.005 --> 33:28.841
Yeah. Mine, too.

33:34.222 --> 33:37.767
Why don't you try the key, see
if we can't get it started.

33:42.188 --> 33:45.233
I should've paid attention
in auto shop. Ouch.

33:59.622 --> 34:02.125
What did you do?
Well, I was...

34:02.208 --> 34:05.253
I have no idea. I don't...

34:05.336 --> 34:07.088
I don't know anything
about cars.

34:07.171 --> 34:10.341
I was just trying
to be manly.

34:10.425 --> 34:13.511
That was great, thank you.
You saved my day.

34:13.594 --> 34:17.098
Of course I did.
I said I would.

34:18.766 --> 34:20.518
Where you headed?

34:20.601 --> 34:22.728
I'm not sure.

34:22.812 --> 34:24.188
Bear Mountain, maybe.

34:24.272 --> 34:26.524
I just threw my stuff
in the car and took off.

34:26.607 --> 34:27.692
Had to get out of the city.

34:27.775 --> 34:28.860
How come?

34:28.943 --> 34:30.945
'Cause summer's over
and I missed it.

34:32.071 --> 34:35.616
I work all the time. It makes
me feel old. I don't know.

34:40.788 --> 34:41.831
Oh!

34:44.000 --> 34:45.793
Well, thanks again.

34:50.672 --> 34:52.049
So, what's the problem?

34:52.132 --> 34:54.427
My problem seems
to be solved.

34:54.510 --> 34:56.012
Oh, no.

34:56.094 --> 34:58.097
Wait a second.
The car's fine.

34:58.181 --> 34:59.390
Yeah, but listen, honey.

34:59.474 --> 35:02.226
I gave up on four calls
hauling my ass out to you.

35:02.310 --> 35:03.853
Okay? That's $100 to me,

35:03.936 --> 35:05.897
so if nothing's wrong
with this car now

35:05.980 --> 35:08.566
there will be when I bring it
down to the city. Okay?

35:08.649 --> 35:09.734
Everything all right?

35:09.817 --> 35:12.195
Everything's
peaches, mac.

35:19.786 --> 35:22.079
You're Billy Chapel.

35:22.163 --> 35:23.706
I can't believe it.

35:23.790 --> 35:26.667
It's a pleasure to meet you.
I can't believe this.

35:27.251 --> 35:28.795
Oh, I'm sorry.

35:31.130 --> 35:33.674
You know, you're the greatest
freaking ballplayer out there.

35:33.758 --> 35:36.135
I'm sorry.
But you really are.

35:36.219 --> 35:39.680
I'm gonna go get that.
You stay right here, okay?

35:42.350 --> 35:44.143
Billy Chapel.

35:44.227 --> 35:46.646
Nice to meet you.
Jane Aubrey.

35:48.523 --> 35:51.359
You know, I got this problem.

35:51.442 --> 35:54.695
See, I'd like to keep
talking with you,

35:54.779 --> 35:56.781
but I got to go to work.

36:00.493 --> 36:01.953
Just a sec. Hey!

36:04.205 --> 36:06.165
I'll get there
when I get there.

36:06.249 --> 36:08.584
Can you do me a favor?
Anything.

36:08.668 --> 36:10.169
We got a bum deal
on this rental here,

36:10.253 --> 36:11.921
so if you could...

36:12.004 --> 36:14.048
If you could haul this
back to town for us,

36:14.131 --> 36:15.675
I'd really appreciate it.

36:15.758 --> 36:17.385
I can't take that.

36:17.468 --> 36:20.388
Wait a second.
What are you doing?

36:21.472 --> 36:23.307
You like baseball?
What?

36:23.391 --> 36:24.392
Baseball.

36:24.475 --> 36:25.852
No, not really. Hey...

36:25.935 --> 36:27.812
You ever been?

36:27.895 --> 36:29.063
No.

36:29.146 --> 36:30.982
Would you like to go?

36:33.442 --> 36:36.487
Would you like to go
to a baseball game with me?

36:36.571 --> 36:39.365
Billy, if she don't
want to go, I'll go.

36:40.867 --> 36:42.743
Don't let that happen.

37:02.972 --> 37:05.975
Lady, you can't just stand
in the middle like that.

37:06.058 --> 37:07.143
Oh. Sorry.

37:07.226 --> 37:09.186
Let me see your ticket.

37:09.270 --> 37:12.106
You're with the players'
wives. Follow me.

37:19.322 --> 37:21.908
Thanks. Excuse me.

37:22.950 --> 37:24.785
Sorry. Sorry.

37:25.786 --> 37:28.164
Hey there, excuse me.

37:28.247 --> 37:29.999
Who are you here with, honey?

37:30.082 --> 37:31.667
Billy Chapel.

37:31.751 --> 37:33.294
Oh, how nice.

37:36.797 --> 37:38.633
This week's blonde.

37:47.600 --> 37:50.102
No, stay.
You're cool. Trust me.

37:50.186 --> 37:51.938
I've been there, all right?

37:52.021 --> 37:53.731
I'm Kisha Birch.

37:53.814 --> 37:54.815
Hi.
Hi.

37:54.899 --> 37:56.442
Jane Aubrey.
Nice to meet you.

37:56.525 --> 37:58.277
Strike three!

38:08.120 --> 38:09.997
You got a ball?
Yeah.

38:19.256 --> 38:21.759
You don't lose much, do you?

38:21.884 --> 38:23.719
I lose. I've lost.

38:25.346 --> 38:29.392
About 134 times.

38:29.475 --> 38:30.685
Oh!

38:32.353 --> 38:34.772
That's over, like,
15 years, okay?

38:34.855 --> 38:36.357
Oh!

38:36.440 --> 38:38.651
You count them?

38:38.734 --> 38:40.945
We count everything
in baseball. I mean,

38:41.529 --> 38:43.280
God, that's all we do.

38:45.199 --> 38:47.410
All right, quit stalling.

38:47.493 --> 38:48.661
What?

38:48.744 --> 38:52.248
You haven't told me
anything about you. Nothing.

38:52.331 --> 38:55.292
I figured if I kept
my mouth shut,

38:55.376 --> 38:57.920
I could pass
for elegant and mysterious.

38:58.004 --> 39:00.256
You're forgetting
I saw you on the highway,

39:00.965 --> 39:03.384
kicking the hell out
of your car.

39:06.887 --> 39:08.180
Where are you from?

39:08.264 --> 39:09.265
Oh, God.

39:12.810 --> 39:15.062
Three questions.

39:15.146 --> 39:17.356
Syracuse, New York.
That's one.

39:22.278 --> 39:24.613
What are the pads for?

39:24.697 --> 39:28.075
This one is my article on
lip gloss for <i>Elle</i> magazine

39:28.159 --> 39:31.245
this one is on skin peels,
and my grocery list.

39:35.207 --> 39:36.709
Last question.

39:42.798 --> 39:45.051
How do you like to be kissed?

39:50.598 --> 39:53.392
You know, I've always thought

39:53.476 --> 39:56.687
that men and women should
just carry around signs.

39:56.771 --> 39:58.814
You know, if you're poor
and you can't afford it,

39:58.898 --> 40:01.692
you would make yours
out of cardboard and string.

40:01.776 --> 40:04.612
And if you're rich, you could
have it lettered in gold leaf

40:04.695 --> 40:07.615
or pounded out of tin
by Mexican craftsmen,

40:07.698 --> 40:08.866
it doesn't matter.

40:08.949 --> 40:11.327
But you wear them
around your neck. See?

40:11.410 --> 40:15.706
And they say things
like "shallow" or "horny."

40:15.790 --> 40:19.752
It just would be
a hell of a lot easier.

40:21.962 --> 40:23.798
What would yours say?

40:51.492 --> 40:53.953
Billy, isn't this your floor?

40:54.036 --> 40:55.663
I think so.

40:55.746 --> 40:57.998
We've been here twice before.

41:15.349 --> 41:17.059
Good morning.

41:17.143 --> 41:18.602
Good morning.

41:20.062 --> 41:21.438
Got to go.

41:22.898 --> 41:24.150
Sleep as long as you want.

41:24.233 --> 41:26.152
You can take a shower,
anything you want.

41:26.277 --> 41:29.280
Nobody'll bother you
till you take the sign
off the door.

41:29.363 --> 41:30.865
Okay. Thanks.

41:32.283 --> 41:34.285
What's this? A souvenir?

41:35.536 --> 41:37.121
It's my number.

41:40.875 --> 41:42.668
Billy, you don't have
to give me this.

41:42.751 --> 41:47.631
I know I don't have
to do this, but I wanted to.

41:53.762 --> 41:55.806
When will you be back?

41:55.890 --> 41:57.224
I already checked.

41:57.308 --> 42:00.519
Four weeks from Thursday I'll
be back in New York, so...

42:01.979 --> 42:03.564
That Thursday night

42:04.481 --> 42:07.234
meet me in the bar
downstairs at 10:00, okay?

42:08.194 --> 42:10.446
I'll be there waiting for you.

42:12.031 --> 42:13.490
If you don't show up,

42:13.574 --> 42:16.368
if you leave me standing
in that bar, it'll ruin this.

42:16.911 --> 42:19.997
Well, then I guess
I'll just have to show up.

42:20.080 --> 42:21.665
I'm serious.

42:22.750 --> 42:25.252
I'll be there, Jane, okay?

42:26.086 --> 42:27.922
Okay, Billy Chapel.

42:51.570 --> 42:56.992
Birch, baby! Kiss that bitch
goodbye! Take it over!

42:58.744 --> 43:00.496
Clear the mechanism.

43:15.135 --> 43:16.929
You look old, Davis.

43:18.430 --> 43:20.015
Are we that old?

43:27.273 --> 43:29.566
<i>And the fastball
sinks at the knees,</i>

43:29.650 --> 43:31.735
<i>picks up the corner
and the count 0 and 1.</i>

43:31.819 --> 43:34.029
Don't smile at me, Davis.
I hate that.

43:34.113 --> 43:36.240
<i>It was a sad day in Detroit</i>

43:36.323 --> 43:38.575
<i>when Gary Wheeler,
the owner of the Tigers</i>

43:38.659 --> 43:40.911
<i>and a somewhat
beleaguered franchise,</i>

43:40.995 --> 43:44.498
<i>was forced to trade Davis
Birch, who was a free agent.</i>

43:44.581 --> 43:47.418
<i>Detroit could not come up
with his monetary demands.</i>

43:47.501 --> 43:51.255
<i>The Yankees were waiting with
open arms and an open wallet.</i>

43:51.839 --> 43:53.757
It was your team, too.

43:55.759 --> 43:57.845
I mean, how much money
we got to make?

43:57.928 --> 44:00.222
You want to see my team?

44:00.723 --> 44:02.599
Let's go play.
That's my team over there.

44:02.683 --> 44:06.103
You got it. I'll be out
in a second, okay?

44:06.186 --> 44:08.355
Billy, are you gonna just
sit there and mope

44:08.439 --> 44:10.274
or are you gonna help?

44:16.155 --> 44:19.700
I ain't carrying no books.
Where's the pillows?

44:26.540 --> 44:28.625
You're the best, kiddo.

44:29.084 --> 44:31.378
The best around.
The worthy opponent.

44:35.341 --> 44:36.967
<i>The 0-1 pitch,</i>

44:37.051 --> 44:39.428
<i>and the bottom just drops
out of it. Strike two.</i>

44:39.511 --> 44:42.014
<i>Look at Birch staring
out at Chapel saying,</i>

44:42.097 --> 44:43.390
<i>"Where's that curveball
coming from?</i>

44:43.474 --> 44:47.061
<i>"You never had that curveball
when we played together."</i>

44:53.192 --> 44:57.029
It don't happen that often,
but I got you mixed up,
don't I?

44:59.990 --> 45:02.368
You're guessing now,
aren't you?

45:04.203 --> 45:06.663
Well, here's your fastball.

45:06.747 --> 45:09.500
Right down the pipe so
you don't walk away thinking

45:09.917 --> 45:11.752
I was afraid
to give it to you.

45:13.379 --> 45:14.380
Strike!

45:14.463 --> 45:17.049
<i>Fastball runs
on the inside corner.</i>

45:17.132 --> 45:18.842
<i>Strike three called.</i>

45:18.926 --> 45:20.844
Jesus, Birch,
I could've hit that.

45:20.928 --> 45:22.805
<i>So, Billy Chapel
all business,</i>

45:22.888 --> 45:24.848
<i>taking care of Birch
on three pitches.</i>

45:24.932 --> 45:26.934
<i>Lenny Howell will follow.</i>

45:28.894 --> 45:30.562
<i>If you don't show up,</i>

45:30.646 --> 45:33.315
<i>if you leave me standing
in that bar, it'll ruin this.</i>

45:52.000 --> 45:53.627
Cab, Mr. Chapel?

45:58.966 --> 46:00.926
You leaving?

46:01.009 --> 46:04.555
Yeah, I was supposed
to meet someone, but they...

46:04.638 --> 46:07.266
I'm sorry.
I wasn't gonna come.

46:07.349 --> 46:08.934
I actually sat
in my apartment,

46:09.017 --> 46:10.144
counting the hours
to the time

46:10.227 --> 46:14.148
when I was not gonna show up
to meet you and then I just...

46:14.940 --> 46:16.358
Oh, God.

46:18.485 --> 46:20.529
Billy Chapel.

46:20.612 --> 46:23.490
Why do you always use
both my names?

46:23.574 --> 46:25.534
So I know
what I'm up against.

46:25.617 --> 46:28.120
I had a great time with you
last month.

46:28.203 --> 46:30.122
It's not that.
Don't get me wrong.

46:30.205 --> 46:32.249
It's just that...

46:32.332 --> 46:35.627
I don't mean to sound like
anything or anything.

46:35.711 --> 46:39.756
But, but I don't do that.

46:39.882 --> 46:41.508
And I'm not saying
anything about it.
What?

46:41.550 --> 46:44.511
I just don't do it,
not since college.
What don't you do?

46:44.595 --> 46:46.263
I just... You know what?

46:46.346 --> 46:48.432
I think I should go home.
Why?

46:48.515 --> 46:51.226
Because I just don't
screw like that!

46:52.186 --> 46:54.938
And I hate that word.

46:55.022 --> 46:56.440
You want the cab,
Mr. Chapel?

46:56.523 --> 46:57.941
Give it to somebody else.

46:58.025 --> 47:01.987
I don't go to hotel rooms
with men I don't know.

47:02.070 --> 47:03.447
Billy, I can't be a groupie.

47:03.530 --> 47:04.781
You're not a groupie, Jane.

47:04.865 --> 47:07.034
You don't look like one
or act like one.

47:07.117 --> 47:08.368
I didn't treat you like one.

47:13.248 --> 47:14.458
Wasn't I a gentleman?

47:14.541 --> 47:16.043
Yes, I know.

47:16.126 --> 47:18.462
But you pull up
out of nowhere,

47:18.545 --> 47:20.881
you start my car,
you make me laugh

47:20.964 --> 47:22.549
and the next thing I know,

47:22.841 --> 47:25.969
I'm at a baseball game
that you win!

47:26.053 --> 47:28.555
I mean, it's so surreal.

47:28.639 --> 47:32.434
Little boys buy cards
with your picture on them.

47:32.518 --> 47:34.645
They buy those for the gum.

47:38.398 --> 47:40.484
God damn it!

47:40.567 --> 47:41.818
What?

47:42.778 --> 47:44.571
God damn what?

47:45.572 --> 47:46.990
I like you.

47:49.284 --> 47:51.328
So what's the problem?

47:51.411 --> 47:54.873
I'm really not at all
the person you think I am.

47:54.957 --> 47:58.085
And I think it would just be
more fair for both of us

47:58.460 --> 48:00.420
for me to just leave.

48:02.881 --> 48:05.425
Well, forget it.

48:09.930 --> 48:14.768
What's the difference?
I mean... What? No.

48:15.102 --> 48:17.521
Here, give me the thing.

48:17.604 --> 48:20.566
What's the difference
between the real you

48:20.899 --> 48:22.693
and this other you?

48:22.818 --> 48:25.654
The real me is...

48:26.947 --> 48:28.949
The real me is plain,

48:29.032 --> 48:32.327
uninteresting and hates
sexy underwear

48:32.411 --> 48:34.871
because it's really
uncomfortable.

48:39.126 --> 48:41.461
All right.
So, the real you is a bummer.

48:41.545 --> 48:45.090
This can't be what you were
looking for from this evening.

48:45.173 --> 48:47.759
Be totally honest with me.

48:47.843 --> 48:51.555
That day I fixed your car,
Jane, I got lucky.

48:51.638 --> 48:53.890
And maybe you got lucky, too.

48:54.808 --> 48:59.229
I mean, I know we don't
know each other so well,

48:59.313 --> 49:02.774
but that's what I was hoping.

49:02.858 --> 49:07.112
I mean, we don't have to...
We could, like, walk.

49:07.195 --> 49:10.741
I mean, we could walk like...
We can just walk.

49:10.824 --> 49:11.992
Walk?

49:13.952 --> 49:15.454
I could walk.

49:18.540 --> 49:21.418
We don't have to talk
so much either.

49:21.501 --> 49:22.502
Okay.

49:49.112 --> 49:50.739
Border collie.

49:52.783 --> 49:54.993
My dad loved
the Blue Heelers.

49:55.077 --> 49:56.662
Is he still alive?

49:57.204 --> 49:59.039
No, they're both gone.

50:00.248 --> 50:02.918
Him first,
and then her within a year.

50:06.088 --> 50:07.381
He was a good man.

50:08.215 --> 50:11.009
Very tall. Very reserved.

50:11.718 --> 50:14.554
Passionately in love
with two things,

50:15.222 --> 50:18.642
my mother and baseball.

50:18.725 --> 50:20.686
Then he was a lucky man.

50:23.605 --> 50:24.731
Okay.

50:29.069 --> 50:30.153
Okay.

50:34.408 --> 50:39.579
So, how do we do this?
How does this work, Billy?

50:39.663 --> 50:40.747
I told you,

50:40.872 --> 50:43.375
I have to be here next month
for a couple of days.

50:43.458 --> 50:45.252
I want to see you.

50:45.335 --> 50:46.753
Okay.

50:47.379 --> 50:48.505
Okay.

50:52.426 --> 50:55.929
So, when you're away

50:56.012 --> 50:59.474
I'll live my life
and you'll live yours.

50:59.808 --> 51:03.687
And none of this stupid, bullshit,
why-didn't-you-call-me crap.

51:03.770 --> 51:05.689
And what you do
when you're not with me

51:05.772 --> 51:08.358
has nothing to do with me,
and vice versa.

51:08.442 --> 51:13.780
No questions asked.
No worrying. No obsessing.

51:17.367 --> 51:19.202
That sounded perfect.

51:21.455 --> 51:23.123
Good night.
Good night.

51:55.322 --> 51:57.908
My back keeps breaking out.

51:57.991 --> 52:00.577
Candy says it's gross.

52:00.660 --> 52:02.204
Use the loofah.

52:03.413 --> 52:05.457
The what?

52:05.540 --> 52:08.001
The loofah. It exfoliates.

52:09.419 --> 52:11.755
You're losing it
over this girl.

52:17.010 --> 52:20.222
I met this woman in New York.

52:20.305 --> 52:22.682
I'm thinking
of asking her down.

52:23.850 --> 52:25.101
Call her.

52:25.185 --> 52:28.063
No, you know,
it's not... It's casual.

52:29.272 --> 52:31.900
I've seen her a few times
over the winter in New York

52:31.983 --> 52:33.860
when I happened to be there.

52:35.278 --> 52:36.571
Call her.

52:45.372 --> 52:46.790
Hello?

52:46.873 --> 52:50.919
<i>I'm having this problem
with my skin peel.</i>

52:52.212 --> 52:53.505
I was just thinking about you.

52:53.588 --> 52:55.257
<i>Yeah? What were you thinking?</i>

52:55.340 --> 52:58.802
<i>I was wondering when
you play your first series
against the Yankees.</i>

52:58.885 --> 53:00.303
Jane, come down here.

53:00.387 --> 53:01.471
<i>What?</i>

53:01.555 --> 53:02.639
Come see me.

53:02.722 --> 53:04.391
Come spend the weekend.
Meet my friends.

53:04.474 --> 53:06.226
I don't know, Billy.

53:06.309 --> 53:08.687
<i>What do you mean,
you don't know?</i>

53:08.770 --> 53:12.274
I've got a ton of work to do,
and you know,

53:12.399 --> 53:15.110
I can't afford
to be running off...
<i>So I'll pay.</i>

53:15.193 --> 53:16.236
No.

53:17.779 --> 53:19.281
It's not that.

53:20.991 --> 53:22.409
Look, we made the rules.

53:22.492 --> 53:23.743
I think we should
stick to them.

53:23.827 --> 53:26.621
There's no rules about having
fun. I mean, that's bullshit.

53:26.705 --> 53:28.248
<i>Why is it bullshit?</i>

53:28.331 --> 53:31.209
Because if all you wanna do
is have fun, then you would
come here down here

53:31.293 --> 53:33.336
'cause this is fun.

53:33.420 --> 53:35.422
You know who sat
in the bleachers last Sunday?

53:35.505 --> 53:37.465
<i>Who?</i>

53:37.549 --> 53:38.717
Sandy Koufax.

53:39.175 --> 53:41.386
You are such a...
Sandy Koufax.

53:41.469 --> 53:44.347
You are such a guy.
You are like the ultimate guy.

53:44.431 --> 53:45.515
What? You don't like guys?

53:45.599 --> 53:46.975
I need a regular guy,

53:47.058 --> 53:49.060
not the guy on
the Old Spice commercial.

53:49.144 --> 53:50.562
It was Right Guard.

53:50.645 --> 53:51.771
<i>What?</i>

53:52.814 --> 53:55.525
It was Right Guard,
that commercial.

53:55.609 --> 53:58.695
I was being
metaphorical, Billy.

53:58.778 --> 54:01.573
Look, this is crazy.
What am I supposed to do?

54:01.656 --> 54:04.492
I'm supposed to run down
there and meet Sandy Koufax,

54:04.576 --> 54:07.120
get his autograph and sleep
with Mr. Right Guard?

54:07.203 --> 54:09.289
What are you so afraid of?

54:09.372 --> 54:10.749
<i>I'm not afraid.</i>

54:12.542 --> 54:15.003
<i>I can't be a groupie.</i>

54:15.086 --> 54:18.757
You know, that's
the second time you used
that word to me, Jane,

54:18.840 --> 54:21.843
<i>and it didn't really go down
that well the first time.</i>

54:21.968 --> 54:23.053
Now you're mad.

54:23.136 --> 54:26.556
No, I'm not mad.
I'm just pissed off.

54:26.640 --> 54:27.641
<i>Billy, that's not fair.</i>

54:27.724 --> 54:30.060
I'm gonna hang up now,
all right?
<i>Let's just start from...</i>

54:30.143 --> 54:31.227
I'll call you another time.

54:31.311 --> 54:34.064
Wait. No.
When will you call me?

54:34.147 --> 54:36.775
<i>Like, when I don't feel
like killing you.</i>

54:42.739 --> 54:44.115
I told her.

54:45.867 --> 54:49.371
So, I haven't seen you
around much lately.

54:50.830 --> 54:52.749
I've been working hard.

54:52.832 --> 54:56.628
Yeah, well.
All work and no play.

55:22.320 --> 55:24.364
All I've got is
my toothbrush

55:24.447 --> 55:26.616
and a bathing suit
I bought at the airport.

55:30.537 --> 55:34.165
You're not smiling.
You're annoyed.
No.

55:34.249 --> 55:35.625
I'm an idiot.

55:35.709 --> 55:37.752
No, I'm an idiot.

55:38.420 --> 55:40.046
Jane, listen to me.

55:40.130 --> 55:43.800
No matter what happens
in the next five minutes,

55:43.883 --> 55:48.263
I want you to know
that when I opened this door

55:48.346 --> 55:51.349
I was so happy to see you
that my heart leapt.

55:52.600 --> 55:55.979
It leapt in my chest. Okay?

55:58.231 --> 55:59.482
Okay.

55:59.566 --> 56:01.943
Hey, Billy,
can I borrow your...

56:02.902 --> 56:04.279
Blow dryer?

56:15.415 --> 56:16.750
Don't go.

56:22.380 --> 56:24.049
It's not your...

56:26.468 --> 56:27.469
Jane!

56:27.552 --> 56:30.513
I have terrible timing.
I've always had it.

56:30.597 --> 56:33.433
You know, that's why
I failed at acting

56:33.600 --> 56:36.144
and skiing and table tennis.

56:36.227 --> 56:39.689
I should have known when
the only flight to Lauderdale

56:39.773 --> 56:41.232
was at 6:10 a.m.

56:41.316 --> 56:43.860
and the only rental car
I could get

56:43.943 --> 56:45.862
was this ridiculous Lincoln.

56:45.945 --> 56:50.033
The car is perfect.
It's perfect.

56:50.116 --> 56:51.701
That girl...

56:51.785 --> 56:55.371
Please. You don't have to do
this. I'm not angry or hurt.

56:55.455 --> 56:57.415
We're not anything.
You're fine.

56:57.499 --> 57:00.001
You can do whatever you want.
I know I can do... I just...

57:00.085 --> 57:01.127
I don't want her.

57:01.211 --> 57:03.421
Then what is she doing here?

57:04.672 --> 57:07.342
Well, I like her.
She's my masseuse.

57:13.807 --> 57:17.352
It's never quite
how you play it in your head.

57:19.521 --> 57:22.232
What about the whole
deal thing?

57:22.315 --> 57:23.441
What deal?

57:23.525 --> 57:26.569
You know, you do what you do,
I do what I do.

57:26.653 --> 57:28.154
You believed that?

57:28.238 --> 57:31.074
I was lying.
I was trying to be the man.

57:31.157 --> 57:33.201
And I was doing
a damn good job of it

57:33.284 --> 57:35.662
until you invited me
down here.

57:38.248 --> 57:39.833
You were right.

57:42.585 --> 57:44.379
I was afraid.

57:44.462 --> 57:46.506
I was afraid you were
gonna break my heart

57:46.589 --> 57:49.092
into 1,000 pieces.

57:50.260 --> 57:52.011
I'm sorry. Jane.

57:59.477 --> 58:02.021
I've been thinking
about you, Jane.

58:03.648 --> 58:06.401
I don't know what I was...
That was a...

58:08.987 --> 58:11.739
All right, tell me what I can
say so you'll believe me.

58:11.823 --> 58:13.366
I believe you.

58:15.451 --> 58:17.078
Then stay.

58:17.162 --> 58:19.372
Please, Jane.
I want you to stay.

58:19.455 --> 58:22.083
This can only end bloody
for me, Billy.

58:23.543 --> 58:26.546
I saved the sign.
You know the "yes" sign?

58:26.629 --> 58:29.883
I pinned it on the wall
in my locker. God damn it!

58:31.426 --> 58:32.927
It was stupid!

58:35.221 --> 58:36.973
<i>Strike three called.</i>

58:37.891 --> 58:39.392
<i>On the corner.</i>

58:41.102 --> 58:43.062
Strike three!
<i>Fastball, got him looking.</i>

58:43.146 --> 58:45.565
<i>That's strikeout number five
for Billy Chapel</i>

58:45.648 --> 58:47.817
<i>and he is really
on a roll now.</i>

58:47.901 --> 58:51.196
<i>Franklin, obviously
annoyed at what he thinks
is a bad call</i>

58:51.279 --> 58:53.948
<i>is muttering as he goes up
the first base line.</i>

58:54.032 --> 58:56.242
<i>Bill Murdie showing
some patience,</i>

58:56.326 --> 58:58.161
<i>but right back at him,
ready to bite.</i>

58:58.244 --> 58:59.662
<i>Here's that pitch again.</i>

58:59.746 --> 59:02.749
<i>It looked like it was in the
heart of the strike zone.</i>

59:02.832 --> 59:05.710
<i>It's a little surprising
that Franklin was so annoyed.</i>

59:05.793 --> 59:07.879
<i>And it looks like
for Bill Murdie,</i>

59:07.962 --> 59:10.590
<i>the pot is
about ready to boil over.</i>

59:11.049 --> 59:13.676
<i>So, a dominant inning
for Billy Chapel,</i>

59:13.760 --> 59:15.220
<i>striking out the side.</i>

59:22.435 --> 59:24.395
You're in the zone.

59:24.479 --> 59:25.855
<i>Number 24.</i>
Feels good.

59:25.939 --> 59:28.274
<i>Now, there's
Mickey Hart, 0 for 1.</i>

59:28.358 --> 59:30.235
<i>No score, fourth inning.</i>

59:30.318 --> 59:31.778
<i>Jack Spellman doing well.</i>

59:31.861 --> 59:34.030
<i>Has allowed only two hits
to the Tigers</i>

59:34.113 --> 59:37.367
<i>and meanwhile, Billy
Chapel in perfect control.</i>

59:38.952 --> 59:41.579
Oh, Mickey'll be gone
next year, too.

59:42.622 --> 59:45.458
Poor guy.
Never could get a break.

59:49.212 --> 59:50.797
Where was that catch
he missed?

59:51.297 --> 59:52.715
The one that hit him?

59:53.508 --> 59:56.052
They still play that on
Diamond Vision all the time.

59:56.135 --> 59:59.472
"There goes another
rubber tree plant."

01:00:04.686 --> 01:00:05.937
Fenway.

01:00:29.669 --> 01:00:31.796
Everything's all right, man.

01:00:37.927 --> 01:00:41.014
Guess that looked pretty funny
out there today, huh?

01:00:43.391 --> 01:00:45.685
Probably end up
on ESPN or something.

01:00:45.768 --> 01:00:49.230
Lot of shit ends up
on ESPN I don't think
is very funny, Mick.

01:00:49.314 --> 01:00:51.232
Phone call, Mr. Chapel.

01:00:52.483 --> 01:00:53.943
There's a bunch of cameras
out there,

01:00:54.027 --> 01:00:55.695
waiting to make
a joke of this, Mick.

01:00:56.362 --> 01:00:57.822
So you can either stop,

01:00:58.239 --> 01:01:00.742
give them the sound bite,
do the dance,

01:01:01.409 --> 01:01:03.077
or you hold your head up
and walk by,

01:01:03.161 --> 01:01:04.704
and the next time
we're in Boston

01:01:05.204 --> 01:01:09.584
we'll go out there and we'll
work the wall together.

01:01:09.667 --> 01:01:12.378
Don't help them make
a joke out of you.

01:01:17.467 --> 01:01:20.303
Old school, baby. He's right.

01:01:21.554 --> 01:01:22.889
- Chapel.
<i>- It's Jane.</i>

01:01:22.972 --> 01:01:25.141
<i>I got your number
from the front office.</i>

01:01:25.224 --> 01:01:27.977
<i>I hope that it's okay.</i>
No, that's all right.

01:01:28.061 --> 01:01:30.646
Don't worry about it.
What's wrong?

01:01:30.730 --> 01:01:32.398
<i>Something's happened.</i>

01:01:32.482 --> 01:01:34.901
<i>It's my daughter.
She ran away. And...</i>

01:01:34.984 --> 01:01:37.487
Your daughter?
<i>I'll tell you.
I don't have time now.</i>

01:01:37.570 --> 01:01:40.323
<i>But she's there in Boston.
Her father lives there.</i>

01:01:40.406 --> 01:01:42.241
<i>Oh, God.
We had a fight and she...</i>
All right.

01:01:42.325 --> 01:01:45.828
Jane, just slow down,
all right? Just slow down.

01:01:45.912 --> 01:01:48.998
<i>She climbed down the fire escape
and went to Penn Station</i>

01:01:49.082 --> 01:01:51.918
<i>got on a train to go to her
father, but he's not there.</i>

01:01:52.001 --> 01:01:53.669
What's the address?

01:01:53.753 --> 01:01:55.630
<i>8245 Clackton.</i>

01:01:55.713 --> 01:01:57.507
<i>What's her name?</i>

01:01:57.590 --> 01:01:58.674
<i>Freedom.</i>

01:01:58.758 --> 01:01:59.884
<i>Freedom?</i>

01:01:59.967 --> 01:02:03.262
<i>Scared you, didn't I?
Heather. It's Heather.</i>

01:02:13.481 --> 01:02:14.774
Heather?

01:02:20.113 --> 01:02:21.656
It's okay.

01:02:21.739 --> 01:02:25.118
I'm the guy your mom said
was coming to get you.

01:02:28.621 --> 01:02:33.042
Let's get out of here
before we get our asses
kicked twice in one night.

01:02:36.421 --> 01:02:37.672
Heather?

01:02:41.217 --> 01:02:43.511
You're Heather.

01:02:43.594 --> 01:02:45.847
And you're
the baseball player.

01:02:51.310 --> 01:02:53.479
My mom can do nothing normal.

01:03:10.163 --> 01:03:11.456
Shut up.

01:03:19.964 --> 01:03:22.383
Do you want something?

01:03:22.467 --> 01:03:24.093
I'll have a V8.

01:03:25.511 --> 01:03:28.806
What is it with single men
and V8 juice?

01:03:28.890 --> 01:03:32.310
I mean, my dad's fridge has
nothing but mustard in it,

01:03:32.393 --> 01:03:35.354
but when I come to visit,
it has mustard, fish sticks,

01:03:35.438 --> 01:03:38.357
and this big jug of V8 Juice.

01:03:38.441 --> 01:03:40.651
Like, if he makes me
choke down a glass,

01:03:40.735 --> 01:03:43.196
he's being healthy
and fatherly.

01:03:45.907 --> 01:03:47.575
Well, I like V8.

01:03:49.577 --> 01:03:50.578
It's nutritious.

01:03:58.961 --> 01:04:01.422
So, are you
my mom's boyfriend?

01:04:01.506 --> 01:04:03.090
I'm not sure.

01:04:05.593 --> 01:04:07.637
But you've slept with her.

01:04:15.394 --> 01:04:20.691
V8. It's a refreshing blend
of eight vegetable juices.

01:04:32.745 --> 01:04:35.581
What did you and
your mother fight about?

01:04:42.255 --> 01:04:46.259
I didn't come home from school
when I was supposed to

01:04:46.342 --> 01:04:48.719
because I was
with Mark Elton and...

01:04:49.887 --> 01:04:53.224
She freaked out
because he has facial hair

01:04:53.307 --> 01:04:55.434
and his parents
are never home.

01:04:55.893 --> 01:04:58.271
And I said,
"We didn't do anything."

01:04:58.354 --> 01:04:59.605
And she said,
"You could have."

01:04:59.689 --> 01:05:03.985
And I said,
"Well, I might love him."

01:05:04.068 --> 01:05:06.279
And she said,
"You don't know what love is."

01:05:06.362 --> 01:05:08.573
And I said, "Well, I'm gonna
do what I want to do."

01:05:08.656 --> 01:05:11.367
And she said,
"Well, not in this house."

01:05:11.450 --> 01:05:12.451
And...

01:05:13.828 --> 01:05:16.163
So I went to my dad's because

01:05:17.748 --> 01:05:19.542
he doesn't care what I do

01:05:20.960 --> 01:05:22.920
'cause he's stoned
90 percent of the time.

01:05:28.843 --> 01:05:30.261
She just...

01:05:32.263 --> 01:05:35.558
She doesn't want me

01:05:36.809 --> 01:05:38.769
to make the same
mistakes that she did.

01:05:39.687 --> 01:05:42.189
I mean, she had me
when she was 16.

01:05:44.859 --> 01:05:48.487
I know she never had
a love story.

01:05:51.824 --> 01:05:54.994
And now, it's like
she doesn't believe in it.

01:06:11.677 --> 01:06:14.263
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.
I'm sorry, too.

01:06:14.347 --> 01:06:15.848
I'm so sorry.

01:06:21.187 --> 01:06:22.521
Thank you.

01:06:23.814 --> 01:06:25.024
Billy?

01:06:26.525 --> 01:06:27.818
Come up.

01:06:33.032 --> 01:06:35.618
Don't ever do
that again, okay?
Okay.

01:06:35.701 --> 01:06:39.163
We can always work it out,
all right? Just talk to me.

01:06:45.670 --> 01:06:47.463
Honey, you want
some spaghetti?

01:06:47.546 --> 01:06:50.216
No, it's okay. I'm tired.
You sure?

01:06:50.299 --> 01:06:52.677
Yeah. I ate on the plane.
Okay.

01:06:52.760 --> 01:06:55.846
How was it?
It was good.
It was really small.

01:07:47.940 --> 01:07:49.734
She's already asleep.

01:07:52.903 --> 01:07:54.238
Thank you.

01:07:58.033 --> 01:08:00.327
Why didn't you tell me?

01:08:00.411 --> 01:08:01.954
I don't know.

01:08:03.247 --> 01:08:05.499
I protect her, maybe too much.

01:08:06.333 --> 01:08:07.960
Some guys meet her

01:08:08.252 --> 01:08:09.712
and they don't come
around anymore.

01:08:11.130 --> 01:08:13.174
She thinks it's her fault.

01:08:16.301 --> 01:08:18.261
You want some tea,
or something? I could make...

